<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-809] Bad bug in ChunkedWriter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-809</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.mahout.text.ChunkedWriter has a bug, that causes data loss, if the maximal chunk size is reached. The first chunk is overwritten, then it continues normally.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This is caused in line 58:&lt;br/&gt;
writer = new SequenceFile.Writer(fs, conf, getPath(currentChunkID++), Text.class, Text.class);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix should look like this:&lt;br/&gt;
writer = new SequenceFile.Writer(fs, conf, getPath(++currentChunkID), Text.class, Text.class);&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Occurred on single node, not tested on cluster.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
